[assistant] 抽取并记录信息: {"user_identity": "", "user_preference": "", "research_direction": "Music Therapy and Music Medicine Interventions", "filter_requirements": "近两年", "rejection_reasons": "", "other_info": "Types of studies: All randomized clinical trials and quasi‐randomized trials (trials that allocate participants to a treatment by using a method that is not random such as alternate group assignment or date of birth) in any language, published and unpublished, were eligible for inclusion.\n\nTypes of participants: The review included studies of men, women, and children, inpatient or outpatient, with confirmed coronary heart disease (CHD). The original review included several studies with participants who did not have confirmed CHD (e.g., cardiac diagnostic procedures). For this update we limited the inclusion criteria to studies where all participants had confirmed CHD. Therefore, studies involving cardiac procedures for diagnostic purposes as well as studies with participants with suspected myocardial infarction were not included in this review.\n\nTypes of interventions: The review included all studies in which any form of participation in music (e.g. listening to music, singing, playing music) was compared with any form of standard treatment. Studies using music therapy interventions, as defined by the authors, as well as music medicine interventions, as defined by the authors, were considered for inclusion. We did not use length or frequency of music sessions as inclusion criteria for this review.\n\nTypes of outcome measures: Psychological distress including anxiety, depression, and mood; Quality of life. Psychological distress including anxiety, depression, and mood; Quality of life. Heart rate; Respiratory rate; Systolic blood pressure; Diastolic blood pressure; Mean arterial pressure; Myocardial oxygen demand; Oxygen saturation; Peripheral skin temperature; Hormone levels; Pain; Opioid intake; Quality of sleep; Length of hospitalization; Duration of cardiac procedure.\n\nPrimary outcomes: Psychological distress including anxiety, depression, and mood; Quality of life.\n\nSecondary outcomes: Heart rate; Respiratory rate; Systolic blood pressure; Diastolic blood pressure; Mean arterial pressure; Myocardial oxygen demand; Oxygen saturation; Peripheral skin temperature; Hormone levels; Pain; Opioid intake; Quality of sleep; Length of hospitalization; Duration of cardiac procedure.\n\nWhere more than one measure per outcome was used for psychological distress, quality of life, and pain, we gave preference to measures taken using validated instruments. Primary outcomes and pain were rated by the participant. Physiological responses were recorded by an observer who may or may not have been blinded."}
[assistant] 抽取并记录信息: {"other_info": "这是一个非常详细的查询记录，包含了多个数据库（如CINAHL、PsycINFO、EMBASE等）的关键词及其对应的上下文信息。这些信息可以帮助您理解每个数据库中关键词的使用范围和研究主题的方向。\n\n以下是对此查询记录的简要分析：\n\n### 1. **CINAHL (OvidSp)**\n   - **关键词**：音乐、音乐疗法、心肌梗死、心脏病、心血管疾病等。\n   - **上下文**：\n     - 包括音乐与心脏相关的研究，如心肌梗死、心脏病和心血管疾病。\n     - 关注研究类型，包括随机对照试验（Randomized controlled trials）、对照研究（Controlled studies）等。\n\n### 2. **PsycINFO (OvidSP)**\n   - **关键词**：音乐、音乐疗法、心肌梗死、心脏疾病等。\n   - **上下文**：\n     - 包含与音乐对心脏健康影响相关的心理学和医学研究，如 myocardial infarction（心肌梗死）、angina pectoris（冠脉性胸痛）等。\n     - 关注研究类型，包括随机对照试验、假设检验等。\n\n### 3. **EMBASE (OvidSP)**\n   - **关键词**：音乐疗法、音乐、心脏疾病、心血管疾病等。\n   - **上下文**：\n     - 包含与音乐疗法在心脏病治疗中的应用相关的临床研究和实验设计。\n     - 关注研究类型，如随机对照试验、临床试验等。\n\n### 4. **LILACS (Virtual Health Library)**\n   - **关键词**：心脏相关疾病（如心肌梗死、冠脉手术等）。\n   - **上下文**：\n     - 主要关注与心脏手术和心血管疾病相关的文献，但不支持时间限制。\n\n### 5. **Social Science Citation Index (ISI)**\n   - **关键词**：音乐、音乐疗法、心脏相关疾病等。\n   - **上下文**：\n     - 包含与音乐疗法在心理治疗中的应用研究，关注研究类型如随机对照试验和假设检验。\n\n### 6. **Appendix 3. Journals Handsearched**\n   - **关键词**：音乐疗法、音乐治疗学期刊等。\n   - **上下文**：\n     - 列出了多个音乐疗法相关期刊的出版年份范围，帮助您筛选文献来源。\n\n---\n\n如果您需要更具体的信息或帮助选择适合的研究主题，请提供更多细节。"}
